message.body: Do you think we're going to need to know which bacteria we used? Like the plasmid experiment we used 2054, 754, and 760?
I doubt it. That would be really dumb
Okay. That's what I was thinking too.
Bryan just asked me to send him notes, or at least I'm assuming it's Bryan.
The lab notes? What a punk
Yeah. I sent them to him. No good ever comes from him when he texts me. It's only ever to get something. Tsk tsk.
Okay...for the generalized transduction lab, did we select Km-R and screen Cm-R?
Yeah I think so
Okay so then how is there a chance that we may get cm sensitive colonies?
Yeah I wrote the same thing. It doesn't make any sense.
Ah! Stupid freaking quiz.
Well at least it's the last lab
That's true.
And you should feel proud knowing you single handedly allowed Bryan to pass this course
Aww you can't reneg. At least stick with your decision.
I am. Let's face it, I think I would've given it to him no matter what.
Lol probably.
The grading thing says half our grade is this lab report, but he hasn't said anything about the lab report
Then maybe we'll all get As and go home skipping. Or more will ride on this quiz. How bad do you think it'll be? I didn't start studying until I text you at 11:30.
Hopefully not too bad. I just started studying now
Hah! Awesome.
We better not need minutia from that stupid chart
I would be pissed! I only studied the antibiotics we used in lab: vancomycin, tetracycline, chloramphenicol, and rifampin. And I only know what they target.
What was E15 and E2 from the antibiotic lab
Yeah. I think it's part of the penicillin family. Erythromycin I believe.
It's not in the chart
O wait yes it it. It's under macrolides
Oh good to know.
